                    "company": "GREAT TEACHER STEVE",
                    "description": "\ud83d\ude80 \ud835\udc03\ud835\udc08\ud835\udc12\ud835\udc02\ud835\udc0e\ud835\udc15\ud835\udc04\ud835\udc11 . \ud835\udc02\ud835\udc0e\ud835\udc0d\ud835\udc0d\ud835\udc04\ud835\udc02\ud835\udc13 . \ud835\udc0b\ud835\udc04\ud835\udc00\ud835\udc11\ud835\udc0d\n\nSteven Asei-Dantoni Nkou\u00e9, known as GREAT TEACHER STEVE, is a firm believer in the magic of interconnectedness and the transformative power of community. His mission is to empower learners to embrace their true potential and become catalysts for positive change. He firmly believes that innovation begins with authentic human connections.\n\n\ud835\udc00\ud835\udc1b\ud835\udc28\ud835\udc2e\ud835\udc2d \ud835\udc0c\ud835\udc1e:\n\n\ud83c\udf93 Education & Innovation Evangelist:\nInternationally renowned lecturer, researcher, and consultant in the fields of learning and innovation. Committed to driving meaningful change in education and organizations.\n\n\ud83c\udf0d Human Innovation Design Advocate:\nPassionate about creating safe spaces for individuals and teams to unlock their full potential. Dedicated to fostering a culture of continuous learning and innovation through deep human interactions, rooted in the philosophy of Ubuntu.\n\n\ud83c\udf10 Global Impact:\nProudly associated with esteemed institutions and organizations, including the EDF Group, Caisse d\u2019Epargne, UNICEF, Adecco, Leiden University, Excelia Business School, and The Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs.\n\n\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f International Speaker & Visionary:\nInvited to prestigious platforms to share insights. Notable appearances include speaking on the future of education at Gauteng's 5th Youth Expo at the personal invitation of former South African President Kgalema Motlanthe. Featured as a TEDx speaker in 2016, offering fresh perspectives on redesigning the classroom learning experience.\n\n\ud835\udc12\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc2b\ud835\udc2f\ud835\udc22\ud835\udc1c\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc2c:\n\n\ud83d\udde3\ufe0f Keynote Speaker: Engage and inspire your audience with thought-provoking talks that drive change.\n\n\ud83d\udcda University Lecturer: Nurturing the leaders of tomorrow through dynamic and innovative teaching methods.\n\n\ud83d\udd0d Workshops & Seminars: Facilitating transformative learning experiences for organizations and individuals.\n\n\ud83e\udd1d Consultancy: Partnering with organizations to reshape team dynamics and foster a culture of continuous learning for innovation.",
